+   This document defines the following terms:
+
+   *  Access Control: Rules and policies that define which actions a Domain
+      Manager or Remote Management Client is permitted to perform on the
+      SCHC Rules and Context.
+
+   *  Management request processing: The process by which a NETCONF, RESTCONF,
+      or CORECONF request is received, authenticated, validated against
+      access control policies, and applied to the SCHC configuration.
+
+   *  Rule Manager (RM) / Instance Manager: The logical component on the Endpoint
+      responsible for processing management requests, enforcing access control,
+      and managing the lifecycle and configuration of SCHC Instances.
+
+   *  Context: A Set of Rules (SoR) together with metadata, shared by two or
+      more Instances, as defined in [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture].
 
